You can use setVisible, but not on the panel you you add to the tabbed pane. The tabbed pane actually uses setVisible on the components added to it. So if you say &quot;setVisible(false);&quot; when you click on the tab the component will be shown.

The example below shows this behavior. When you select the tab, the visibility of JPanel a gets set. The visibility of `toggle` doesn&#39;t get set because it is a child of `a`.

That way calling `toggle.setVisible(false);` it will be hidden when the tab is selected.

For your example, 

    JPanel wrapper = new JPanel();
    wrapper.add(regPanel);
    tabbedPane.addTab(&quot;Register Tab&quot;, null, wrapper, null);
    
That way you can call `setVisible` on the `regPanel` and it will stay hidden when the tab is selected.

